      "explanation": "The tabulation algorithm begins by constructing the **exploded supergraph**. Each node is a pair `<program_point, dataflow_fact>`. We start with a single dataflow fact: the **zero fact** (lambda), which represents \"no taint\".\n\nProgram points for `main`: entry, `t = source()`, `propagate(t)`, exit.\nProgram points for `propagate`: entry, `sink(val)`, exit.\n\nCall edges connect `propagate(t)` in main to `propagate_entry`, and return edges connect `propagate_exit` back to `main_exit`.\n\nThe worklist is **seeded** with the initial path edge: `<main_entry, lambda> -> <main_entry, lambda>`. This represents: at the entry of main, the zero fact (no taint) holds.",
