      "action": "Process source() return -- generate taint fact",
      "explanation": "The algorithm pops `<main_entry, lambda> -> <main_entry, lambda>` from the worklist and propagates it forward.\n\nAt `t = source()`, the **flow function** for a taint analysis recognizes that `source()` introduces a new taint fact. The flow function maps:\n- `lambda -> lambda` (zero fact propagates -- other untainted data remains untainted)\n- `lambda -> t` (a **new** taint fact `t` is generated by the source call)\n\nTwo new path edges are added to the worklist:\n- `<main_entry, lambda> -> <t_assign, lambda>` (zero fact passes through)\n- `<main_entry, lambda> -> <t_assign, t>` (new taint fact `t` is born here)\n\nThe `factsAt` map now shows that at `t_assign`, both `lambda` and `t` hold.",
