      "action": "Process call to propagate() -- map t to val",
      "explanation": "The algorithm processes path edges reaching `call_propagate`. At the call site `propagate(t)`, two things happen:\n\n**1. Call-to-return edge** (intraprocedural): The zero fact `lambda` passes directly from the call site to the return site (`main_exit`), representing data in main that is unaffected by the call.\n\n**2. Call-to-start edge** (interprocedural): The taint fact `t` is mapped to the callee's formal parameter `val`. This creates a new path edge in `propagate`: `<propagate_entry, val> -> <propagate_entry, val>`.\n\nThe worklist now contains the new path edge in `propagate`, seeding the analysis of the callee with the taint fact `val`.\n\nThis is the key interprocedural step -- taint crosses the procedure boundary from actual argument `t` to formal parameter `val`.",
